<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">SOS 211</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Sociological Perspectives</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">27.02.2021</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">This course discusses how different Sociological Perspectives approach social relations and processes and make sense of society. At the beginning of the course, the theories of the leading founders of the history of sociology, namely Emile Durkheim, Karl Marx and Max Weber, are emphasized. In the following weeks, structuralism and post-structuralism movements from contemporary sociological theories are examined.</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=131865&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Sociology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5946</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">SOS 221</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Statistics I</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">7</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">27.02.2021</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">The aim of this course is to introduce students to the basics of Statistics. The subjects form the background of the statistical analysis of the second semester course Sos222.
Tables and charts
Data research
Average, median and crest
Variance and standard deviation
Addition and multiplication rules
Dependent probability
Binomial distribution
Poisson distribution</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=131880&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
</Row>
<Row>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Sociology</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">5946</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">SOS 231</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">Society and Economics</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3+0+0</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">3</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">4</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">15.09.2022</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">National income
Money
Instability in economic life and stability policies
International economic relations
Economic growth and development</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">https://obs.acibadem.edu.tr/oibs/bologna/progCourseDetails.aspx?curCourse=131866&amp;lang=en</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String">OK</Data></Cell>
<Cell ss:StyleID="Text"><Data ss:Type="String"></Data></Cell>
